<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 13 at 7:58PM EST  by NWS Detroit</headline>
<description>...LAKE EFFECT SNOW SHOWERS INCREASING COVERAGE AND INTENSITY AND
A WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IS IN EFFECT THIS EVENING...
WEATHER...
* A band of lake effect snow organizing near the I-96/696
corridor as of 8 PM moves toward the M-59 corridor and then the
I-69 corridor through 11 PM.
* Snow accumulation around 1 inch is likely at any given location
as the band moves northward.
* Westerly wind gusting in the 30 mph range supports blowing
snow.
IMPACTS...
* Increasing rates of snow add a fresh accumulation on area
roads.
* Heavier bursts of snow showers produce low visibility for
drivers. There may be rapid fluctuations of visibility.
&amp;&amp;
PRECAUTIONARY/PREPAREDNESS ACTIONS...
* Motorists are urged to use caution and account for hazardous
driving conditions by driving at slower speed.
* Prepare, plan and stay informed. Visit http://go.usa.gov/c7kkP</description>
